    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,IDatatype> create(IAUTOSAR asr)
        Creates the default data types in a dedicated package below the AUTOSAR package of a system model. If the package "AUTOSAR" or "DataTypes" already exist, the data types are added into the already existing package. If any of the data types exists, the data type elements themselves are retrieved and their properties are updated. The properties of the data types have been taken from autosar_swc.arxml AUTOSAR Version 3.0, with the exception of "UInt8_n", which has been taken from the ASR Com SWS
        Parameters:
        asr - the AUTOSAR tag below which the "DataTypes" package is created or retrieved.
        Returns:
        map String → IDatatypes of all default data types that were either created or retrieved
        Since:
        2008.b

      • cloneDataType

        public static IDatatype cloneDataType(IDatatype sourceType,
                                      java.lang.String shortName)
        Creates a clone of a handed over scalar data type. The handed over datatype has to be added to an IARPackage by the caller.
        Parameters:
        sourceType - handed over source IDatatype
        shortName - short name the cloned data type will obtain
        Returns:
        the cloned data type
        Since:
        15.0
